def: The fossil root stem of a coal plant of the genus Sigillaria.
To strip or wear off the skin of; to abrade; to gall; to breakand remove the cuticle of, in any manner, as by rubbing, beating, orby the action of acrid substances.
A shell of the genus Nucula. To be, or lie, in a nutshell, tobe within a small compass; to admit of very brief or simpledetermination or statement. "The remedy lay in a nutshell." Macaulay.
A situation or position beneath. Kane.
A composition in a soft, rural style, generally in 6-8 or 12-8time.
